formula_49 and formula_50 are the pass band ripple frequency and maximum ripple attenuation in dB

formula_51 and formula_52 are the stop band frequency and attenuation at that frequency in dB

formula_3 is the minimum number of poles, the order of the filter.

&quot;ceil&quot;[] is a round up to next integer function.

=== Setting the cutoff attenuation ===
Pass band cutoff attenuation for Chebyshev filters is usually the same as the pass band ripple attenuation, set by the computation above. However, many applications such as diplexers and triplexers, require a cutoff attenuation of -3.0103 dB in order to obtain the needed reflections. Other specialized applications may require other specific values for cutoff attenuation for various reasons. It is therefore useful to have a means available of setting the Chebyshev pass band cutoff attenuation independently of the pass band ripple attenuation, such as -1 dB, -10 dB, etc. The cutoff attenuation may be set by frequency scaling the poles of the transfer function.

The scaling factor may be determined by direct algebraic manipulation of the defining Chebyshev filter function, formula_1, including formula_7 and formula_56. The general definition of the Chebyshev function, formula_57 is required, which may be derived from the Chebyshev Polynomials equations, and the inverse Chebyshev function, formula_58. To keep the numbers real for values of formula_59, complex hyperbolic identities may be used to rewrite the equations as, formula_60 and formula_61.

Using simple algebra on the above equations and references, the expression to scale each Chebyshev poles is:

